
    BANYANA Banyana midfielder Thembi Kgatlana says she’s honoured to be recognised by continental football authority, the Confederation of African Football, following an impressive year.The 21-year-old Banyana star has been nominated as Women’s Player of the Year, while Banyana were nominated as National Women’s Team of the Year.This follows Banyana’s impressive triumph at the Cosafa Women’s Championship in Zimbabwe, where Kgatlana played an influential role for the team and was named Player of the Tournament.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");<a href="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=/8900/24.com/Web/DailySun/Sport/Article&sz=300x250&c=1487345955&t=artid%3d4f882051-3413-43e8-973f-b566fa4fc5bd%26accreditation%3ddaily+sun%26posno%3d2" target="_blank"><img src="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=/8900/24.com/Web/DailySun/Sport/Article&sz=300x250&c=1487345955&t=artid%3d4f882051-3413-43e8-973f-b566fa4fc5bd%26accreditation%3ddaily+sun%26posno%3d2" border="0" alt=""></a>Talking to SunSport the University of Western Cape student described 2017 as a year to remember in her football career. In addition to her Cosafa accolade, Kgatlana walked away with the University Sport South Africa (USSA) Football Women’s Player of the Tournament and Top Goal-Scorer gongs, and was part of the USSA national team at the World Student Games in Taiwan three months ago. And now the Caf nomination.Kgatlana said: “I don’t know what to say, although I must admit I was not surprised because I have been working extremely hard this year. Still, to be nominated as one of the best women players on the continent will serve as motivation and is one of my top highlights of my time with the national team.”“Credits also goes to my teammates. We are nominees for Caf National Women’s Team of the Year. We’ve made it despite all the challenges.”) Caf Confederation Cup runners-up SuperSport United have been nominated in the Club of the Year category, while SuperSport striker Jeremy Brockie, who finished the Confederation Cup campaign as top scorer with 10 goals, got an African Player of the Year nomination alongside Mamelodi Sundowns goalkeeper Denis Onyango. Onyango is also nominated as Player of the Year (Based in Africa). Amajita Under-20 winger Luther Singh has been nominated for the Caf Youth Player of the Year award.
